<TITLE> Kuakata residents remain indoors </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kuakata, Nov 14 (bdnews24.com) -- The local administration asked Kuakata residents to move to safety Wednesday evening after the weather office sounded great danger signal No. 10 for Mongla Port. Kuakata resident Monju Mong told bdnews24.com that loudspeaker announcements had advised locals to seek cover in the nearby cyclone shelter. "Some people have gone to the cyclone shelter, mainly those who live on the Bay side of the embankment. But most people haven't gone as it is only drizzling with very little wind at the moment," Monju said Wednesday. "I'm worried it may be the lull before the storm really hits," he added. Local fishermen in the area secured their boats behind the protective embankment in preparation for the storm, and locals have largely remained indoors. b
